%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Restaurant%20To%20Pay%20Workers%20%24140%2C000%20After%20Hiring%20Priest%20To%20Confess%20'Sins'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20restaurant%20in%20California%20has%20been%20ordered%20to%20pay%20a%20total%20of%20%24140%2C000%20in%20back%20wages%20and%20damages%20to%2035%20employees%20by%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Labor.%20According%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxnews.com%2Fus%2Fcalifornia-restaurant-pay-140k-after-making-employees-confess-workplace-sins-supposed-priest%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFox%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20restaurant%20hired%20a%20%26quot%3Bsupposed%26quot%3B%20priest%20to%20have%20the%20employees%20confess%20their%20%26quot%3Bworkplace%20sins%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChe%20Garibaldi%20Inc.%2C%20which%20operates%20the%20Taqueria%20Garibaldi%20Mexican%20restaurant%20in%20Sacramento%20has%20been%20fined%20after%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor.%20The%20federal%20investigators%20are%20calling%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20shameless%26quot%3B%20acts%20of%20corruption%20an%20employer%20has%20taken%20against%20its%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnder%20oath%2C%20an%20employee%20of%20Taqueria%20Garibaldi%20explained%20how%20the%20restaurant%20offered%20a%20supposed%20priest%20to%20hear%20their%20workplace%20'sins'%20while%20other%20employees%20reported%20that%20a%20manager%20falsely%20claimed%20that%20immigration%20issues%20would%20be%20raised%20by%20the%20department's%20investigation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Regional%20Solicitor%20of%20Labor%20Marc%20Pilotin%20in%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20employer's%20despicable%20attempts%20to%20retaliate%20against%20employees%20were%20intended%20to%20silence%20workers%2C%20obstruct%20an%20investigation%20and%20prevent%20the%20recovery%20of%20unpaid%20wages.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20owner%20hired%20the%20fake%20priest%20to%20hear%20confessions%20during%20work%20hours%20and%20%26quot%3Bget%20the%20sins%20out%26quot%3B%2C%20including%20asking%20them%20if%20they%20had%20been%20late%20for%20work%2C%20stolen%20money%20from%20the%20restaurant%20or%20had%20%26quot%3Bbad%20intentions%26quot%3B%20toward%20their%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20investigators%20also%20found%20out%20that%20the%20employees%20were%20deprived%20of%20their%20overtime%20wages%2C%20which%20violates%20the%20Fair%20Labor%20Standards%20Act%2C%20according%20to%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20also%20learned%20the%20employer%20paid%20managers%20from%20the%20employee%20tip%20pool%20illegally%2C%20threatened%20employees%20with%20retaliation%20and%20adverse%20immigration%20consequences%20for%20cooperating%20with%20the%20department%2C%20and%20fired%20one%20worker%20who%20they%20believed%20had%20complained%20to%20the%20department%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20DOL%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Labor%20and%20its%20Solicitor's%20Office%20will%20not%20tolerate%20workplace%20retaliation%20and%20will%20act%20swiftly%20to%20make%20clear%20that%20immigration%20status%20has%20no%20bearing%20on%20workers'%20rights%20under%20the%20Fair%20Labor%20Standards%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20Regional%20Solicitor%20of%20Labor%20Marc%20Pilotin%20said%20in%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaqueria%20Garibaldi%20has%20agreed%20to%20pay%20out%20%2470%2C000%20in%20back%20wages%2C%20%2470%2C000%20in%20damages%20and%20%245%2C000%20in%20civil%20penalties%20%26quot%3Bdue%20to%20the%20willful%20nature%20of%20their%20violations%2C%20Fox%20News%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690185360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F9mhegd48_taqueria-garibaldi_625x300_24_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-restaurant-ordered-to-pay-workers-140-000-after-hiring-fake-priest-to-confess-sins-4235796%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20owner%20hired%20the%20fake%20priest%20t