setalvad-supreme-court-gujarat-high-court-bail%5C%22%3Egranted%3C%2Fa%3E%20regular%20bail%20to%20social%20activist%20Teesta%20Setalvad%2C%20setting%20aside%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98perverse%E2%80%99%20order%20denying%20her%20bail%20in%20the%20alleged%20evidence%20fabrication%20case.%20The%20following%20day%2C%20on%20July%2020%2C%20a%20city%20sessions%20court%20in%20Ahmedabad%20rejected%20her%20application%20seeking%20discharge%20from%20the%20same%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditional%20Sessions%20Judge%20A.R.%20Patel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fahmedabad%2Fevidence-fabrication-case-teestas-discharge-plea-rejected%2Farticleshow%2F101998898.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Edismissed%3C%2Fa%3E%20her%20plea%20with%20the%20observation%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20my%20clear%20opinion%20that%20there%20is%20enough%20prima%20facie%20evidence%20to%20frame%20charges%20against%20the%20accused%20persons%20looking%20at%20the%20accusations%20levelled%20by%20the%20prosecution%20and%20the%20material%20supplied%20to%20substantiate%20the%20accusations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fahmedabad-court-rejects-teesta-setalvads-discharge-plea-in-2002-riots-evidence-fabrication-case%2Farticle67101482.ece%5C%22%3E%20asked%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20prosecution%20and%20defence%20to%20%E2%80%98open%20the%20case%E2%80%99%20(start%20trial%20proceedings)%20from%20July%2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20has%20been%20written%20about%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20indictment%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20perverse%20reasoning%20in%20dismissing%20Setalvad%E2%80%99s%20bail%20application.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20if%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20in%20rejecting%20her%20bail%20is%20to%20be%20accepted%2C%20then%20no%20application%20for%20bail%20at%20a%20pre-trial%20stage%20could%20be%20entertained%20unless%20the%20accused%20files%20an%20application%20for%20quashing%20the%20proceedings%20under%20Section%20482%20CrPC%20or%20Articles%20226%20or%2032%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20That%20Setalvad%20did%20not%20use%20these%20remedies%20before%20seeking%20bail%20was%20used%20against%20her%20by%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20oral%20observations%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20during%20the%20hearing%20of%20her%20appeal%20against%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20dismissal%20suggest%20that%20the%20prosecution%20case%20against%20her%20is%20equally%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20true%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%2C%20in%20Paragraph%2043%20of%20its%20order%2C%20clarified%20that%20none%20of%20the%20observations%20made%20in%20the%20impugned%20high%20court%20order%20and%20any%20(sic%20for%20none)%20of%20the%20observations%20made%20in%20the%20July%2019%2C%202023%20order%20would%20influence%20the%20trial%20court%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20the%20trial.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20ASJ%20could%20not%20be%20faulted%20for%20rejecting%20most%20of%20Setalvad%E2%80%99s%20contentions%20which%20found%20resonance%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20observed%20so%20in%20Paragraph%2043%20of%20its%20July%2019%2C%202023%20order%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20routine%2C%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20the%20impression%20of%20influencing%20the%20trial%20court%20to%20follow%20its%20reasoning%20which%20it%20applied%20in%20the%20bail%20order.%C2%A0%20Yet%2C%20the%20dissonance%20between%20the%20apex%20court%20and%20the%20trial%20court%20while%20deciding%20similar%20issues%20suggests%20that%20the%20rot%20afflicting%20the%20lower%20judiciary%20is%20much%20deeper%20than%20what%20it%20appears%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20affidavit%20before%20the%20sessions%20court%20opposing%20her%20plea%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20had%20stated%20that%20the%20accused%20could%20not%20be%20discharged%20because%20she%20abused%20the%20trust%20of%20the%20victims%20of%20the%202002%20riots%20by%20creating%20forged%20documents%20in%20their%20name%20and%20attempted%20to%20implicate%20innocent%20people%20using%20forged%20papers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gujarat%20government%20cited%20the%20statements%20of%20Rais%20Khan%20Pathan%2C%20who%20once%20worked%20with%20Setalvad%E2%80%99s%20NGO%20Citizens%20for%20Justice%20and%20Peace%20(CJP).%20Pathan%20had%20alleged%20that%20all%20the%20affidavits%20of%20riot%20victims%20were%20prepared%20by%20her%20while%20the%20victims%20were%20asked%20to%20sign%20on%20blank%20papers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20government%20also%20relied%20on%20another%20affidavit%20filed%20by%20Narendra%20Brahmbhattm%2C%20who%20alleged%20that%20the%20late%20Congress%20leader%20Ahmed%20Patel%20had%20paid%20Rs%2030%20lakh%20to%20Setalvad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%2C%20in%20its%20July%2019%2C%202023%20order%2C%20however%2C%20refrained%20from%20observing%20anything%20on%20that%20issue%2C%20as%20in%20its%20view%2C%20a%20detailed%20elaboration%20of%20evidence%20must%20be%20avoided%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20consideration%20of%20grant%20of%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bench%20noted%20some%20aspects%2C%20which%20emerge%20from%20the%20record%2C%20which%20are%20of%20significance.%20Apart%20from%20noting%20her%20gender%20which%20merited%20grant%20of%20bail%2C%20the%20bench%20noted%20that%20the%20offences%20alleged%20against%20her%20relate%20to%202002%20and%20going%20by%20the%20assertions%20in%20the%20FIR%2C%20pertain%20to%20documents%20which%20were%20sought%20to%20be%20presented%20and%2For%20relied%20upon%20till%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20orally%20observed%20during%20the%20hearing%20makes%20it%20far%20more%20significant%20than%20what%20it%20had%20explicitly%20mentioned%20in%20its%20order.%20%E2%80%9CSection%20194%20would%20not%20be%20applicable%20according%20to%20the%20definition%20of%20evidence%20in%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%20otherwise%2C%20it%20would%20have%20to%20be%20thrown%20into%20the%20dustbin%20if%20your%20contention%20is%20accepted%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20who%20presided%20over%20the%20bench%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-high-court-order-perverse-contradictory-five-questions-teesta-setalvad-bail-233123%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20observing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20had%2C%20keeping%20propriety%20in%20view%2C%20refrained%20from%20pronouncing%20on%20the%20merits%20of%20applicability%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1274033%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%2594Whoever%2520gives%2520or%2520fabricates%2520false%2Clife%255D%252C%2520or%2520with%2520rigorous%2520imprisonment%5C%22%3ESection%20194%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20this%20case.%20However%2C%20the%20bench%20had%20recorded%20the%20submission%20of%20senior%20counsel%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20who%20argued%20on%20behalf%20of%20Setalvad%2C%20which%20was%20not%20contradicted%20by%20the%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%2C%20S.V.%20Raju.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20submitted%20that%20Section%20194%20IPC%20only%20dealt%20with%20the%20evidence%20recorded%20before%20the%20court.%20Sibal%20contended%20that%20since%20there%20is%20no%20material%20to%20show%20that%20Setalvad%20had%20fabricated%20false%20evidence%20intending%20thereby%20to%20cause%20or%20knowing%20it%20to%20be%20likely%20that%20she%20would%20thereby%20cause%20anyone%20to%20be%20convicted%20of%20an%20offence%2C%20which%20is%20capital%2C%20the%20case%20taken%20at%20its%20face%20value%20would%20not%20bring%20it%20under%20the%20purview%20of%20Section%20194%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetalvad%E2%80%99s%20discharge%20application%20before%20the%20Ahmedabad%20sessions%20court%20further%20substantiates%20the%20case%20for%20non-applicability%20of%20Section%20194%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2023%2F25725%2F25725_2023_4_301_45290_Judgement_19-Jul-2023.pdf%5C%22%3EJuly%2019%2C%202023%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20makes%20clear%2C%20Raju%20had%20no%20specific%20answer%20to%20this%20contention%2C%20apart%20from%20his%20fanciful%20claim%20that%20Setalvad%20was%20involved%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20crime%E2%80%9D%20of%20attempting%20to%20convict%20innocent%20citizens%20for%20offences%20punishable%20with%20capital%20punishment%20and%20destabilise%20the%20democratically%20elected%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20single%20judge%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%2C%20Justice%20Nirzar%20S.%20Desai%2C%20on%20July%201%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fteestaatulsetalvadvsstateofgujarat-479111.pdf%5C%22%3Erefrained%20%3C%2Fa%3Efrom%20examining%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20case%20for%20applicability%20of%20Section%20194%20IPC%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20there%20was%20no%20need%20to%20deal%20elaborately%C2%A0%20with%20the%20evidence%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20considering%20bail%2C%20and%20also%20because%20Setalvad%2C%20by%20not%20availing%20the%20legal%20remedies%20to%20challenge%20the%20FIR%2C%20could%20not%20do%20so%20later%20at%20the%20time%20of%20seeking%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECuriously%2C%20however%2C%20as%20revealed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20July%2019%2C%202023%20bail%20order%2C%20ASG%20Raju%20submitted%20during%20the%20hearing%20that%20the%20single%20judge%20of%20the%20high%20court%20%3Cem%3Eprima%20facie%20%3C%2Fem%3Efound%20that%20the%20ingredients%20to%20constitute%20an%20offence%20under%20Section%20194%20IPC%20were%20present%20and%20a%20%3Cem%3Eprima%20facie%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%20had%20been%20made%20out%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20rightly%20rejected%20her%20bail%20application%20(Paragraph%2021).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaju%E2%80%99s%20claims%20were%20apparently%20incorrect%2C%20as%20the%20single%20judge%20had%20expressly%20refrained%20from%20reaching%20a%20finding%20on%20the%20applicability%20of%20Section%20194%20IPC%2C%20to%20avoid%20examination%20of%20evidence%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20considering%20bail%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMerits%20of%20discharge%20application%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetalvad%20filed%20her%20discharge%20application%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1056165%2F%5C%22%3ESection%20227%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20the%20CrPC.%20Under%20this%20provision%2C%20if%20upon%20consideration%20of%20the%20record%20of%20the%20case%20and%20the%20documents%20submitted%20therewith%2C%20and%20after%20hearing%20the%20submissions%20of%20the%20accused%20and%20the%20prosecution%2C%20the%20judge%20considers%20that%20there%20is%20not%20sufficient%20ground%20for%20proceeding%20against%20the%20accused%2C%20he%20shall%20discharge%20the%20accused%20and%20record%20his%20reasons%20for%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FIR%20against%20Setalvad%2C%20former%20State%20Director-General%20of%20Police%20R.B.%20Sreekumar%20and%20former%20IPS%20officer%20Sanjiv%20Bhatt%20was%20registered%20by%20a%20police%20officer%20with%20the%20Crime%20Branch%20Police%20Station%2C%20Ahmedabad%20city%20pursuant%20to%20the%20judgment%20and%20order%20passed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20June%2024%2C%202022.%C2%A0%20In%20paragraph%2088%20of%20this%20judgment%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20observed%20that%20a%20coalesced%20effort%20of%20disgruntled%20officers%20of%20the%20State%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20along%20with%20others%2C%20was%20to%20create%20sensation%20by%20making%20revelations%20which%20were%20false%20to%20their%20knowledge%20and%20pursuing%20the%20proceedings%20for%2016%20years%20to%20keep%20the%20pot%20boiling%20for%20ulterior%20motive.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20observed%3A%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20matter%20of%20fact%2C%20all%20those%20involved%20in%20such%20abuse%20of%20process%2C%20need%20to%20be%20in%20the%20dock%20and%20proceeded%20with%20in%20accordance%20with%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20above%20observation%20resulted%20in%20the%20state%20filing%20a%20detailed%20FIR%20the%20very%20next%20day%2C%20June%2025%2C%202022%2C%C2%A0%20alleging%20that%20Setalvad%20and%20the%20two%20other%20accused%20had%20conjured%2C%20concocted%2C%20forged%20and%20fabricated%20documents%2C%20including%20fabrication%20of%20documents%20by%20persons%20who%20are%20prospective%20witnesses%20and%20also%20tutoring%20the%20witnesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20affidavits%2C%20which%20are%20alleged%20to%20be%20forged%20by%20the%20FIR%20and%20the%20charge%20sheet%2C%20are%20filed%20by%20different%20witnesses%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Transfer%20Petitions%20filed%20by%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20this%20submission%20by%20Sibal%20during%20Setalvad%E2%80%99s%20bail%20hearing%2C%20but%20refrained%20from%20commenting%20on%20this%20aspect%2C%20for%20reasons%20of%20propriety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20July%2019%20bail%20order%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20Sibal%E2%80%99s%20submission%20that%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20Setalvad%20being%20made%20party%20in%20the%20proceedings%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20observations%20in%20paragraph%2088%20of%20the%20Zakia%20Ahsan%20Jafri%20case%20could%20not%20have%20been%20used%20against%20her.%20The%20bench%20tersely%20observed%3A%20%E2%80%9CJudicial%20propriety%20would%20not%20permit%20us%20to%20delve%20into%20those%20issues.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20discharge%20application%2C%20Setalvad%20had%20argued%20that%20no%20grounds%20exist%20against%20her%20even%20prima%20facie%20to%20connect%20her%20to%20the%20alleged%20offences%2C%20much%20less%20to%20proceed%20further%20or%20to%20face%20rigours%20of%20trial%20as%20there%20is%20nothing%20to%20connect%20with%20the%20alleged%20substantive%20offences%20for%20which%20chargesheet%20has%20been%20filed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetalvad%20has%20contended%20in%20her%20discharge%20application%20that%20to%20be%20convicted%20under%20Sections%20468%2C%20469%20or%20471%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20that%20the%20accused%20should%20have%20committed%20forgery%20as%20defined%20under%20Section%20463%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelying%20on%20Section%20463%20IPC%2C%20she%20submitted%20that%20unless%20one%20makes%20a%20false%20document%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20alleged%20that%20she%20has%20committed%20any%20forgery%20even%20if%20she%20has%20intent%20to%20cause%20damage%20or%20injury%20to%20public%20or%20any%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaking%20of%20a%20false%20document%20is%20defined%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1745798%2F%5C%22%3ESection%20464%20IPC%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Setalvad%20pointed%20out%20in%20her%20application%20for%20discharge%20that%20under%20Section%20464%20IPC%2C%20a%20person%20is%20said%20to%20make%20a%20document%20if%20it%20is%20either%20signed%20by%20her%20as%20if%20it%20is%20signed%20by%20the%20other%20or%20executed%20by%20her%20as%20if%20it%20is%20executed%20by%20the%20other.%20Consequently%2C%20when%20all%20the%20affidavits%20presented%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202003%20were%20signed%20and%20affirmed%20before%20a%20Notary%20Public%20by%20the%20respective%20persons%2C%20and%20when%20none%20of%20them%20had%20alleged%20that%20they%20did%20not%20sign%20them%2C%20there%20was%20no%20question%20of%20any%20false%20document%20being%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20significantly%2C%20Setalvad%20underlined%20that%20none%20of%20the%20affidavits%20could%20be%20said%20to%20be%20false%20documents%20under%20the%20first%20part%20of%20Section%20464%20IPC%2C%20and%20that%20even%20the%20prosecution%20had%20not%20laid%20any%20emphasis%20on%20the%20first%20part%20of%20Section%20464%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetalvad%20also%20explained%20in%20her%20application%20for%20discharge%20how%20the%20third%20part%20of%20Section%20464%20IPC%20would%20not%20apply%20to%20her.%C2%A0%20It%20is%20an%20essential%20ingredient%20for%20invocation%20of%20the%20third%20part%20of%20Section%20464%20IPC%20that%20one%20person%20should%20act%20dishonestly%20or%20fraudulently%20as%20defined%20under%20the%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelying%20on%20Sections%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F519920%2F%5C%22%3E23%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F898393%2F%5C%22%3E24%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20IPC%2C%20Setalvad%C2%A0%20submitted%20that%20there%20has%20to%20be%20gain%20of%20property%20to%20the%20person%20acting%20dishonestly%20or%20loss%20of%20property%20to%20the%20person%20who%20is%20deceived.%20%E2%80%9CProperty%20cannot%20mean%20reputation%20or%20image%3B%20it%20only%20means%20either%20immoveable%20or%20moveable%20property%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20underlined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDamage%20to%20the%20reputation%20or%20image%20cannot%20be%20termed%20as%20wrongful%20gain%20or%20wrongful%20loss%2C%20as%20it%20is%20separately%20covered%20as%20an%20offence%20under%20Chapter%2021%20of%20IPC.%20The%20offences%20against%20property%20are%20covered%20in%20Chapter%2017%20of%20IPC%20commencing%20from%20Sections%20378%20to%20462%2C%20all%20of%20which%20only%20deal%20with%20either%20moveable%20or%20immoveable%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetalvad%20submitted%20that%20there%20is%20not%20an%20iota%20of%20allegation%20that%20any%20person%20who%20has%20filed%20affidavits%20in%202003%20had%20wrongfully%20lost%20any%20property%2C%20whether%20moveable%20or%20immoveable%2C%20or%20that%20she%2C%20as%20an%20accused%2C%20had%20gained%20any%20property.%C2%A0%20Therefore%2C%20she%20claimed%20that%20even%20the%20third%20part%20of%20Section%20464%20IPC%20would%20have%20no%20application%20in%20the%20case%20against%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20word%20%E2%80%9Cfraudulently%E2%80%9D%20is%20defined%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1961417%2F%5C%22%3ESection%2025%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20IPC%20as%20follows%3A%20%E2%80%9CA%20person%20is%20said%20to%20do%20a%20thing%20fraudulently%20if%20he%20does%20that%20thing%20%3Cstrong%3Ewith%20intent%20to%20defraud%20but%20not%20otherwise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%9D%20(emphasis%20supplied).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESection%20194%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetalvad%20highlighted%20serious%20violations%20of%20legal%20requirements%20for%20invoking%20Section%20194%20against%20her%20before%20the%20high%20court%20as%20well%20as%20in%20her%20discharge%20application%20before%20the%20sessions%20court.%20Giving%20false%20evidence%20and%20fabricating%20false%20evidence%20%E2%80%93%20offences%20under%20Section%20194%20%E2%80%93%20are%20defined%20under%20Sections%20191%20and%20192%20of%20the%20IPC.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F677888%2F%5C%22%3ESection%20191%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecan%20be%20applied%20only%20when%20the%20applicant%20is%20required%20by%20oath%20or%20by%20any%20express%20provision%20of%20law%20to%20state%20the%20truth%2C%20which%20was%20not%20alleged%20against%20her.%20None%20of%20the%20illustrations%20listed%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1905297%2F%5C%22%3ESection%20192%3C%2Fa%3E%20apply%20to%20Setalvad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20the%20offence%20under%20Section%20194%20IPC%20falls%20under%20Section%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F862299%2F%5C%22%3E195(1)(b)(i)%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20CrPC%20and%20no%20court%20shall%20take%20cognisance%20of%20such%20offence%20except%20on%20a%20complaint%20in%20writing%20of%20that%20court%2C%20or%20by%20such%20officer%20of%20that%20court%20as%20the%20court%20may%20authorise%20in%20writing%20in%20this%20behalf%2C%20or%20some%20other%20court%20to%20which%20that%20court%20is%20subordinate.%20Setalvad%20had%20pointed%20out%20this%20jurisdictional%20flaw%20before%20the%20high%20court%20as%20well%20as%20in%20her%20application%20for%20discharge%20before%20the%20sessions%20court%2C%20but%20in