ity%20clearances.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Christoper%20Nolan's%20%26quot%3BOppenheimer%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Downey%20Jr.%20plays%20Lewis%20Strauss%2C%20the%20man%20who%20wanted%20to%20topple%20J.Robert%20Oppenheimer%20from%20glory%20for%20good.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrauss%20was%20Oppenheimer's%20real-life%20nemesis%20and%20eventually%20helped%20end%20Oppenheimer's%20government%20career.%20The%20pair's%20most%20significant%20disagreement%3F%20Whether%20or%20not%20to%20construct%20the%20most%20powerful%20weapon%20known%20to%20man%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nuclear-weapons-work-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nuclear-weapons-work-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehydrogen%20bomb.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrauss%20was%20born%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Fahf%2Fprofile%2Flewis-strauss%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DStrauss%2520now%2520viewed%2520Oppenheimer%2520as%2C1954%2520for%2520alleged%2520communist%2520ties.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%201896%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20West%20Virginia%20to%20Jewish%20emigrant%20parents%2C%20according%20to%20reporting%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.esquire.com%2Fuk%2Fculture%2Ffilm%2Fa44607738%2Ftrue-story-of-lewis-strauss-oppenheimer%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEsquire%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Despite%20his%20dreams%20of%20studying%20physics%2C%20he%20became%20a%20shoe%20salesman%20to%20support%20his%20father's%20business%20and%20later%20worked%20as%20an%20assistant%20to%20Herbert%20Hoover%20during%20WWI.%20After%20the%20war%2C%20he%20became%20an%20extremely%20successful%20investment%20banker%20and%20worked%20to%20get%20financing%20for%20famous%20projects%20like%20the%20Polaroid%20camera%2C%20and%20served%20as%20a%20naval%20officer%20during%20WWII.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrauss'%20humble%20beginnings%20are%20referenced%20by%20Cillian%20Murphy%20in%20%26quot%3BOppenheimer%26quot%3B%20when%20Murphy%20pokes%20at%20the%20fictional%20Strauss%20by%20asking%20if%20he%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Blowly%20shoe%20salesman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201946%2C%20after%20Strauss%20worked%20in%20weapon%20production%20with%20the%20US%20Navy%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foppenheimer-los-alamos-manhattan-project-scientists-atomic-bomb-petition-2023-7%5C%22%3Ethen-president%20Harry%20Truman%3C%2Fa%3E%20appointed%20him%20to%20the%20Atomic%20Energy%20Commission%2C%20where%20he%20strongly%20advocated%20for%20developing%20thermonuclear%20weapons%20like%20hydrogen%20bombs.%20Thermodynamic%20bombs%20can%20be%20as%20many%20as%20hundreds%20or%20even%20thousands%20of%20times%20as%20strong%20as%20an%20atomic%20bomb%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftechnology%2Fthermonuclear-bomb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrittanica.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20over%20the%20construction%20of%20thermodynamic%20weapons%20put%20Oppenheimer%20at%20odds%20with%20Strauss.%20While%20Oppenheimer%20wanted%20to%20stop%20development%20at%20atomic%20weapons%20and%20share%20data%20about%20US%20weapons%20with%20the%20general%20public%2C%20Strauss%20wanted%20an%20even%20more%20powerful%20bomb%20and%20thought%20the%20US%20should%20keep%20its%20weapon%20developments%20private.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20appointment%20by%20President%20Eisenhower%20as%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20AEC%20in%201953%2C%20Strauss%20continued%20to%20advocate%20for%20the%20development%20and%20testing%20of%20the%20H-bomb.%20He%20also%20began%20his%20campaign%20against%20Oppenheimer%2C%20who%20he%20accused%20of%20being%20a%20communist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrauss%20was%20not%20the%20only%20one%20who%20raised%20concerns%20about%20Oppenheimer's%20communist%20affiliations%20%E2%80%94%20during%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%2C%20staff%20and%20leaders%20also%20questioned%20Oppenheimer's%20loyalties%20over%20the%20years%2C%20as%20the%20famed%20scientist%20had%20a%20long%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flife-career-of-j-robert-oppenheimer-father-of-atomic-bomb-2023-6%23but-he-was-also-openly-reluctant-to-develop-a-hydrogen-bomb-which-would-be-1000-times-more-powerful-than-the-atomic-bomb-23%5C%22%3Ehistory%20of%20associating%20with%20communists%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20an%20affair%20with%20psychiatrist%20Jean%20Tatlock%2C%20played%20by%20Florence%20Pugh%20in%20Nolan's%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20believed%20that%20Strauss'%20motivation%20to%20take%20down%20Oppenheimer%20was%20related%20to%20long-held%20resentment%20after%20Oppenheimer%20publicly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6295760%2Foppenheimer-true-story%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehumiliated%20him%20during%20a%201949%20hearing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20selling%20radioisotopes%20to%20foreign%20nations.%20However%2C%20Strauss%20was%20the%20first%20to%20take%20serious%20action%20about%20Oppenheimer's%20Communist%20accusations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20reenacts%20another%20instance%20when%20Strauss%20feels%20Oppenheimer%20slighted%20him%20%E2%80%94%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falbert-einstein-wrote-letter-us-roosvelt-atomic-bomb-2019-8%5C%22%3EOppenheimer%20and%20Albert%20Einstein%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20played%20by%20Tom%20Conti%2C%20speak%20by%20a%20pond%20after%20Strauss%20offers%20Oppenheimer%20a%20prestigious%20job%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20Advanced%20Study.%20Einstein%20ignores%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Foppenheimer-ending-explained-by-director-christopher-nolan-2023-7%5C%22%3EStrauss%20(it%20is%20later%20revealed%20why%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20but%20this%20further%20angers%20Strauss%2C%20who%20believes%20Oppenheimer%20is%20turning%20the%20scientific%20community%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201953%2C%20the%20AEC%20chairman%20asked%20then-FBI%20Director%20J.%20Edgar%20Hoover%20to%20begin%20surveilling%20Oppenheimer.%20The%20FBI%20built%20a%20case%20against%20him%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Flists%2Foppenheimer-cast-guide-manhattan-project%2Frobert-downey-jr-lewis-strauss%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eillegally%20wiretapping%20Oppenheimer's%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Strauss%20also%20began%20a%20separate%20security%20proceeding%20with%20the%20AEC%20over%20Oppenheimer's%20alleged%20Communist%20ties%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Fahf%2Fhistory%2Foppenheimer-security-hearing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecurity%20clearances%20being%20suspended.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStrauss'%20requests%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20a%20letter%20sent%20to%20Hoover%20by%20the%20former%20Executive%20Director%20of%20Congress's%20Joint%20Atomic%20Energy%20Committee%20William%20Liscum%20Borden%2C%20who%20said%20he%20had%20compiled%20evidence%20that%20Oppenheimer%20was%20%26quot%3Ban%20agent%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20resulted%20in%20Oppenheimer's%20high-level%20government%20security%20clearance%20being%20suspended.%20For%20Borden's%20role%2C%20Nolan%20tapped%20regular%20David%20Dastmalchian%20to%20play%20the%20character.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20physicist%20faced%20a%20Red%20Scare-era%20Senate%20panel%20that%20decided%20although%20he%20was%20loyal%20to%20the%20US%2C%20he%20was%20involved%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Fahf%2Fhistory%2Foppenheimer-security-hearing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20too%20many%20communist%20activities.%3C%2Fa%3E%20His%20security%20clearance%20was%20permanently%20revoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Strauss%2C%20the%20chairman's%20term%20at%20the%20AEC%20ran%20its%20course%2C%20and%20his%20campaign%20against%20Oppenheimer%20eventually%20came%20to%20bite%20him%20in%20the%20back%20%E2%80%94%20during%20his%20appointment%20as%20Secretary%20of%20Commerce%20under%20Eisenhower%2C%20Strauss%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Fvoices%2Foral-histories%2Frobert-r-wilsons-interview%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecame%20so%20unpopular%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20Senate%20Democrats%20that%20his%20confirmation%20did%20not%20go%20through%2C%20and%20his%20time%20in%20government%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DyE-8iTNMlro%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanity%20Fair%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Downey%20said%20director%20Christopher%20Nolan%20wanted%20him%20to%20%26quot%3Btransform%26quot%3B%20into%20someone%20%26quot%3Bsubtle%20and%20plotting%2C%20who%20doesn't%20have%20any%20punchlines%2C%20who's%20only%20charming%20when%20he's%20trying%20to%20manipulate%20or%20undermine%26quot%3B%20to%20play%20Strauss.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNolan%20had%20said%20he%20was%20likening%20it%20a%20bit%20to%20'Amadeus%2C'%20where%20there's%20a%20Mozart%20and%20that's%20not%20you.%20'Sometimes%20you're%20Mozart%2C%20usually%20you're%20Mozart%2C%20this%20time%20you're%20Salieri%2C'%26quot%3B%20Downey%20said%20to%20Vanity%20Fair.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20I%20really%20took%20that%20to%20heart%20as%20him%20kind%20of%20challenging%20the%20entirety%20of%20my%20career%20trajectory%20and%20saying%2C%20'Don't%20use%20any%20of%20those%20things%20that%20have%20served%20you%20well.%20Find%20new%20resources.'%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOppenheimer%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-oppenheimer-has-black-and-white-color-scenes-explanation-2023-7%5C%22%3Eopened%20this%20week%20to%20rave%20revi