and%20payments%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20it%20has%20an%20outsized%20hold%20on%20the%20world%20economy%20and%20is%20often%20overvalued%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wilsoncenter.org%2Farticle%2Fexorbitant-privilege-now-risk-once-and-future-almighty-dollar%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWilson%20Center%20think%20tank%20reported%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20position%20has%20afforded%20the%20US%20what%20Val%C3%A9ry%20Giscard%20d'Estaing%2C%20the%20president%20of%20France%20from%201974%20to%201981%2C%20called%20an%20%26quot%3Bexorbitant%20privilege.%26quot%3B%20One%20facet%20of%20this%20privilege%20is%20that%20the%20US%20might%20not%20run%20into%20a%20crisis%20if%20it%20is%20unable%20to%20pay%20its%20debt%20when%20the%20value%20of%20the%20dollar%20falls%20sharply%20because%20Washington%20could%20simply%20issue%20more%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20means%20that%20countries%20around%20the%20world%20have%20to%20tail%20US%20economic%20and%20monetary%20policies%20closely%20to%20avoid%20a%20spillover%20impact%20on%20their%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20have%20said%20that%20they%20are%20sick%20and%20tired%20of%20US%20monetary%20policies%20holding%20them%20hostage%20%E2%80%94%20going%20as%20far%20as%20to%20say%20that%20the%20US%20has%20been%20an%20irresponsible%20issuer%20of%20the%20world's%20reserve%20currencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fdedollarization-india-pushes-rupee-trade-china-yuan-currencies-russia-sanctions-2023-7%5C%22%3EA%20working%20group%20at%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20now%20pushing%20to%20use%20the%20Indian%20rupee%20for%20trade%20%E2%80%94%20a%20stance%20that%20is%20in%20with%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20vision%20for%20the%20currency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20The%20strong%20USD%20is%20getting%20too%20