a%3E%20In%20April%2C%20Iowa's%20Republican-led%20state%20senate%20voted%2032-17%20to%20pass%20a%20bill%20rolling%20back%20child%20labor%20laws%20in%20the%20state.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fiowa-gop-senate-votes-weaken-child-labor-laws-2023-4%5C%22%3EThe%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20allow%20teens%20to%20work%20until%209%3A00%20p.m.%20during%20the%20school%20year%20and%20until%2011%3A00%20p.m.%20over%20the%20summer%20and%20serve%20alcohol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20industry%20is%20backing%20legislators%20in%20their%20efforts%20to%20loosen%20child%20labor%20laws%2C%20according%20to%20the%20left-leaning%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute.%20The%20National%20Restaurant%20Association%20%E2%80%94%20representing%20over%20100%20restaurant%20corporations%20%E2%80%94%20have%20reportedly%20lobbied%20support%20for%20the%20growing%20pattern.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20risks%20to%20putting%20minors%20around%20alcohol%2C%20analysts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLaws%20that%20lower%20the%20alcohol%20service%20age%20will%20subject%20more%20young%20people%2C%20at%20younger%20ages%2C%20to%20potentially%20dangerous%20working%20conditions%20at%20low%20wages%20%E2%80%94%20all%20in%20service%20of%20employers'%20pursuit%20of%20cheap%20labor%2C%26quot%3B%20Nina%20Mast%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20the%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%2C%20said%20in%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20businesses%20struggle%20to%20hire%20and%20keep%20employees%2C%20fast%20food%20franchises%20and%20factories%20have%20faced%20backlash%20for%20unlawful%20labor%20practices%20involving%20children.%20In%20February%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F7-mcdonalds-locations-in-pennsylvania-broke-child-labor-laws-2023-2%3F_gl%3D1*128xpus*_ga*NDk0OTkwMDg3LjE2NTQ3MDM2MDA.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5MDEzNDYxNS42NjkuMS4xNjkwMTM0Nzk1LjI1LjAuMA..%5C%22%3EPennsylvania%20McDonald's%20locations%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20accused%20of%20breaking%20child%20labor%20laws%20after%2