%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20media%20used%20to%20provide%20nutrients%20to%20the%20soil.%20It%20has%20a%20similar%20setup%20of%20hydroponics%20but%20with%20an%20additional%20fish%20tank%20to%20breed%20fish.%20The%20fish%20excreta%20is%20decomposed%20by%20bacteria%20into%20nitrate%20which%20is%20an%20ideal%20fertiliser%20for%20plants.%20It%20is%20like%20imitating%20the%20river%20ecology.%20Through%20this%20fish%20tank%2C%20water%20is%20regulated%20throughout%20small%20tanks%20that%20hold%20plants%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shashank%2C%20who%20has%20upcycled%20drums%20and%20cans%20to%20use%20as%20fish%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20nitrates%20produced%20by%20fish%20waste%2C%20Shashank%20adds%20iron%20nails%2C%20lime%20and%20egg%20shells%20to%20boost%20iron%20and%20calcium%20nutrients%20in%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20biggest%20advantage%20of%20this%20method%20is%20that%20along%20with%20growing%20food%20without%20soil%20in%20less%20space%2C%20it%20is%20also%20organic.%20Also%2C%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20fertilise%20the%20plants%20individually%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shashank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20aquaponics%20farming%20saves%2080%20percent%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F204078%2Faquaponic-method-farming-how-to-space-requirements-waste-organic-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewater%20required%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20a%20conventional%20farming%20setup%2C%20he%20informs.%20%E2%80%9CFarmers%20can%20also%20harvest%20additional%20income%20by%20breeding%20and%20selling%20edible%20fish%20other%20than%20vegetables%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faquaponics-1-1689666326.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shashank%20gro